column4: Anyone know if Intrepid repositories have changed lately? Like today or yesterday?
Nope.
And Intrepid is beyond it's end of life, so you should upgrade. :)

I'm using an old package, "GPSBabel 1.3.5" from the Intrepid universe repo. I need it for a specific application (but I use Karmic). But today it is no longer installed, an in synaptic it is marked with red color without version numbe.r
And since it's the first day of the month today I suspected that the repo was ended or something like that.
My mirror logs don't show anything changing in intrepid.
And nothing about gpsbabel.
Ok thanks for checkting that, then the issue must have another cause.
checking
Hmm, only recent ref to gpsbabel I can find is from May 31st 17:52UTC.

That is too new for my application. I'm using PyTrainer with my sports watch, and for some reason it only works with gpsbabel 1.3.5 from 2008. They haven't made it work with newer versions for some reason.
And that was just the timestamp on the gpsbabel/ folder changing.

One sec, I will try to look it up (I haven't checked the folder yet, just got the error message that 1.3.5 is needed today, and then saw that it was marked as red in synaptic and no longer having a version number)
The following search found nothing at all, so maybe it has been uninstalled: sudo find -iname gpsbabel
I don't know why it would uninstall itself.
What does 'dpkg -l gpsbabel' show?
Output is at: http://tinypaste.com/03208
If you want to take a quick look, you can connect to my machine using VNC (It is already configured)
!ot | magikc
The issue is now solved. I do not know why it was uninstalled, but now I managed to re-install it.
Thanks for helping me on the way!
No problem.
